The First Lady of the United States, speaking in Suffolk, England, expressed her pride in being part of a military family and commended the service of military families. She acknowledged their crucial role in supporting the military and emphasized the importance of supporting their physical, social, and emotional well-being. The First Lady highlighted the Joining Forces initiative, which aims to address challenges faced by military spouses, provide quality childcare, and ensure access to education. She also stressed the need to improve mental health resources, food security, and support for caregiving families and survivors. The First Lady concluded by recognizing the love and devotion within the military community and expressing gratitude for their service. She then introduced Sydney Glascock, a speaker who comes from a military family and has gained resilience and a global perspective as a result.